  <sys:String x:Key="HelpSectionAbout">ABOUT</sys:String>
  <sys:String x:Key="HelpAboutTitle">What is this app?</sys:String>
  <sys:String x:Key="HelpAboutBody"
    >DeskBrightness uses your Android phone as a light sensor and smoothly adjusts your Windows display brightness from the ambient light it measures.</sys:String
  >
  <sys:String x:Key="HelpSectionSetup">SETUP</sys:String>
  <sys:String x:Key="HelpSetupStep1Title">1. Enable USB debugging on your phone</sys:String>
  <sys:String x:Key="HelpSetupStep1Body"
    >Open Settings → About phone → tap Build number 7 times to unlock Developer options. Go back to Settings → System → Developer options → enable USB debugging. For wireless connection, also enable Wireless debugging and tap Pair with pairing code to see the IP, port and code.</sys:String
  >
  <sys:String x:Key="HelpSetupStep2Title">2. Connect the device</sys:String>
  <sys:String x:Key="HelpSetupStep2Body"
    >Connect via USB, or use the + button next to the device list and select Pair to add a wireless device. Once connected, the device will appear in the list.</sys:String
  >
  <sys:String x:Key="HelpSetupStep3Title">3. Start</sys:String>
  <sys:String x:Key="HelpSetupStep3Body"
    >Select a device from the list and press Connect. DeskBrightness will automatically sense ambient light and adjust your screen brightness in real time.</sys:String
  >
